The paper deals with optimization problems involving submodular functions and matroid constraints, which are common topics in the areas of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), game theory (cs.GT), and information theory (cs.IT). The use of approximation algorithms and regret bounds also suggests a focus on theoretical computer science.
